<p>On first glance, forms are simple to learn. Made up of just a handful of inputs, you can create a form in little time. But when we consider the journeys we need to design, the users we need to design for, the browsers and devices of varying sizes, capabilities and bugs being used; and ensuring that the result is <em>simple and inclusive</em>, form design becomes a far more interesting and bigger challenge.</p>
